\section{Data Collection}

The NatyaVeda dataset was constructed entirely from scratch using a
purpose-built pipeline. Videos were collected from YouTube using \texttt{yt-dlp},
with search queries tailored to each dance form (e.g.,
``Bharatanatyam solo stage performance'', ``Kathak varnam recital''). Videos were
downloaded at a minimum resolution of 720p to ensure sufficient keypoint
visibility.

