\section{Mudra Taxonomy}

The 28 Asamyuta (single-hand) hastas defined in the Natyashastra and
Abhinaya Darpana form the mudra label set: Pataka, Tripataka,
Ardhapataka, Kartarimukha, Mayura, Ardhachandra, Arala, Shukatunda,
Mushti, Shikhara, Kapittha, Katakamukha, Suchi, Chandrakala, Padmakosha,
Sarpashirsha, Mrigashirsha, Simhamukha, Kangula, Alapadma, Chatura,
Bhramara, Hamsasya, Hamsapaksha, Sandamsha, Mukula, Tamrachuda, and
Trishula. These serve as auxiliary supervision targets for the mudra
classification head of DanceFormer.

